1. Bump version number in cmake in format format: v*.*-*
2. Create git tag, Must be same as in cmake format: v*.*.*
3. Create pull request and await approval.
    a. Check that the github runner can succesfully compile the project using workflow dispatch
    command using gh: gh workflow run workflow_pr.yml -r v1.1.0/main
4. Merge with master
5. A runner will pick up and do the following:
 - Create a draft release
 - Compile Ubuntu version
 - Compile Windows version
 - Create Ubuntu/Windows installers
 - Upload to draft release

 It should succeed if worfklow_pr.yml has succeeded as well

6. A user must then edit and publish the release manually